Placeholders (what they are and examples)
%today

Expands to: current date in YYYY-MM-DD (same as %date).
Example: %today ‚Üí 2025-09-21
%date

Expands to: current date in YYYY-MM-DD (alias of %today).
Example: %date ‚Üí 2025-09-21
%time

Expands to: current time in HHMMSS (compact time string).
Example: %time ‚Üí 135445
%Y

Expands to: year, 4 digits.
Example: %Y ‚Üí 2025
%m and %M

Expands to: month, zero-padded (01‚Äì12). Both %m and %M are mapped to month for convenience.
Example: %m ‚Üí 09
%d and %D

Expands to: day, zero-padded (01‚Äì31). Both %d and %D are mapped to day.
Example: %d ‚Üí 21
%H

Expands to: hour (24-hour), zero-padded.
Example: %H ‚Üí 13
%S

Expands to: seconds, zero-padded.
Example: %S ‚Üí 45
%basemodel

Expands to: the first model name from the connected pipe (filename without extension).
Populated from global_values['basemodel'] when pipe_opt is present.
Example: %basemodel ‚Üí modelA (when pipe had modelA, modelB)
%model

Expands to: the model name string (from global_values['model']), typically the first model or the joined model string set by the pipe.
Example: %model ‚Üí modelA
%seed

Expands to: seed value from generation metadata (global_values['seed']).
Example: %seed ‚Üí 12345
%sampler_name

Expands to: sampler name from the pipe metadata.
Example: %sampler_name ‚Üí euler
%scheduler

Expands to: scheduler string from the pipe metadata.
Example: %scheduler ‚Üí normal
%steps

Expands to: steps count (from the pipe metadata).
Example: %steps ‚Üí 20
%cfg

Expands to: CFG value (from the pipe metadata).
Example: %cfg ‚Üí 7.0
%denoise

Expands to: denoise value (from the pipe metadata; V1 sets a default fallback).
Example: %denoise ‚Üí 0.2 or 0.0 if defaulted
%clip_skip

Expands to: clip-skip value (from pipe metadata).
Example: %clip_skip ‚Üí 2
